emotes.msg: No, no I don't want to drink that.
Pretty. But I don't understand what it means.
Well, I suppose I'll take that back. Thanks.
Brentsella!  Why?  Oh, never mind.  Here, you can have this instead.  Take it before I change my mind.
Oh. Yeah, I have that.  If Harlune sent you, you must be getting something back from him, right? I'll tell you what.  There's this... this thing that I need.  From a volcano in the Direlands.
You'll find it at the very bottom, but you must be level 20 or above to get in.  Wait, I'll write you the location.

You got the Water of Lethe!  I don't believe it.  I... I've wanted this for...  Do you know what this does?  Do you know what it's like... the faces of so many waiting behind your eyes every night?  The children asking you where their parents are?
But... Brentsella. I'll lose her too, won't I..?
Here's Harlune's book. Please go, I have to... I need to think. Thank you, but I need to...
Ah, looks like you've found our agent's towel!  Hey, looks like it got rolled in the mud... Anyway, well done!  Here, take these as a reward.
Ah, looks like you've found our agent's towel!  Looks like good old F.P. went swimming or something.  Here's your reward.
Looks like you've lucked out!  Our man F.P. has finished his book, finally!  Here you go...
You found it. Oh bless you, I had lost it, thought I did but someone stole it left me with an empty mug loop on my belt and no cup with which to hold my drink. But bless you, you found it!
It smells of Ayan Baqur, I've caught the scent before, the desert and dirt and the dirty pyreals. So filthy and unclean.
But you, you've a chip or chunk of a tree from the Tiofor Forest around Glenden Wood on you. I can smell it. Might I see it?
You'd rather cast this spell on your own?
Well I can't argue with that.

I have been contracted by the Dereth Exploration Society to help them in their outreach program towards the Isparians who find themselves newly exiled in Dereth. If you collect any of the Society's stamped letters, you may bring them back to me for a reward.
It has also been requested that I start handing out these gems.
By the way -- if you haven't yet done so, you might want to visit Brentsella at the South Outpost, or Mindorla at the East Outpost. They often have tasks for young adventurers.
Oh, Mindorla!  Well, I suppose you want a reward for delivering this to me.  Here it is.
As long as you're here, see what rumors the barkeep is selling.  You might find adventure around here, like I did when I was younger.
Celcynd takes a deep breath of the Bark.
Ah, the smell of fresh firs and the air around Glenden Wood. Indeed that is where this came from. Somewhere near the city and surrounded by firs. May I keep it?
Oh thank you. It reminds me of the area near the Glenden Wood Prison the trees there smell so nice throughout the year.
Bah, I have no time for you now!  Maybe come and see me tomorrow about Mindorla.
What's this? Not the woods. Not the woods!
You will find gems on the table next to me which will allow you to change this weapon into a Heavy, Finesse or Light version.
You must stamp this with a Town Stamp to get a reward.  Please read your Book of Quests to find out how to get a Stamp.
No, this is for you to stamp the letters you find.  Please keep it.
Thank you, you must have journeyed far to get here.  You are a true Explorer!

You will get nothing from me for this. Go explore and find more towns.  The Society Agents in the Gharun'dim towns will exchange a piece of armor for this. If you take this to one of the Sho towns, you will receive a weapon.
There appears to be very little else of use here. No new orders appear to have come down to Commander Kamenua.
